      • from

        @Nonnull
public static ClassBean from(PersistentEObject object)
        Creates a new ClassBean from the given object. The EClass will be found by calling the EObject.eClass() method.

        This method behaves like: of(reference.getName(), reference.getEPackage().getNsURI()).

        Parameters:
        object - the object from which the EClass has to be retrieve with the EObject.eClass() method
        Returns:
        a new ClassBean
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null
        See Also:
        from(EClass)
